## Example 4 — Use Exponential Growth Functions

Mr. Lopez invests `$50 million` at `5%` annual interest.

Use:

`A(t) = a(1 + r)^t`

So:

`A(t) = 50(1.05)^t`

Using technology, after `20` years there will be about:

`$132,664,885.26`

### Watch Out

Keep units in mind. In this lesson, the account balance is measured in millions of dollars.

